cal approach to occult gastrointestinal bleeding. <em>Am J Surg</em> 1992; 163(1):90–92, discussion 92–93.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/0002-9610(92)90258-S">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/1733379/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Surgical+approach+to+occult+gastrointestinal+bleeding&amp;author=A+Szold&amp;author=LB+Katz&amp;author=BS+Lewis&amp;publication_year=1992&amp;journal=Am+J+Surg&amp;pages=90-92&amp;doi=10.1016%2F0002-9610%2892%2990258-S&amp;pmid=1733379">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">7.</div><div id="b7-0300235" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Chong J, Tagle M, Barkin JS, Reiner DKSmall bowel push-type fiberoptic enteroscopy for patients with occult gastrointestinal bleeding or suspected small bowel pathology. <em>Am J Gastroenterol</em> 1994;89 (12):2143–2146.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/7977230/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Small+bowel+push-type+fiberoptic+enteroscopy+for+patients+with+occult+gastrointestinal+bleeding+or+suspected+small+bowel+pathology&amp;author=J+Chong&amp;author=M+Tagle&amp;author=JS+Barkin&amp;author=DK+Reiner&amp;publication_year=1994&amp;journal=Am+J+Gastroenterol&amp;pages=2143-2146&amp;pmid=7977230">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">8.</div><div id="b8-0300235" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Thompson JN, Hemingway AP, McPherson GA, Rees HC, Allison DJ, Spencer JObscure gastrointestinal haemorrhage of small-bowel origin. <em>Br Med J (Clin Res Ed)</e