ospective review of enteroclysis in patients with obscure gastrointestinal bleeding and chronic abdominal pain of undetermined etiology. <em>Dig Dis Sci</em> 2005;50 (4):649–655.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10620-005-2551-7">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15844696/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=A+retrospective+review+of+enteroclysis+in+patients+with+obscure+gastrointestinal+bleeding+and+chronic+abdominal+pain+of+undetermined+etiology&amp;author=A+Malik&amp;author=K+Lukaszewski&amp;author=D+Caroline&amp;publication_year=2005&amp;journal=Dig+Dis+Sci&amp;pages=649-655&amp;doi=10.1007%2Fs10620-005-2551-7&amp;pmid=15844696">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">11.</div><div id="b11-0300235" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Raptopoulos V, Schwartz RK, McNicholas MM, Movson J, Pearlman J, Joffe NMultiplanar helical CT enterography in patients with Crohn’s disease. <em>AJR Am J Roentgenol</em> 1997;169(6):1545–1550.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.2214/ajr.169.6.9393162">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9393162/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Multiplanar+helical+CT+enterography+in+patients+with+Crohn%E2%80%99s+disease&amp;author=V+Raptopoulos&amp;author=RK+Schwartz&amp;author=MM+McNicholas&amp;author=J+Movson&amp;author=J+Pearlman&amp;author=N+Joffe&amp;publication_year=1997&amp;journal=AJR+Am+J+Roentgenol&amp;pages=1545-1550&amp;doi=10.2214%2Fajr.169.6.9393162&amp;pmid=9393162">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label">